value.title: If Biden wins and Dems control Congress, SCOTUS will be expanded: Graham
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and the Democratic Party want to expand the Supreme Court to at least 13 seats to make it liberal if Republicans succeed in confirming Amy Coney Barrett, Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., told "Fox & Friends" on Thursday.

value.title: NYC joining Portland, Seattle to sue Trump admin over defunding for 'anarchist jurisdictions'
value.excerpt: New York City is joining Seattle and Portland, Ore., to file a complaint against the Trump administration in a Seattle court.

value.title: Harris, prominent Democrats listed as 'key contacts' for Biden family business venture projects
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: A list of “key domestic contacts” for a joint venture involving Jim and Hunter Biden and now-bankrupt CEFC China Energy Co. included former Vice President Joe Biden's current running mate Sen. Kamala Harris, among other prominent Democrats, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Linda Ronstadt slams Donald Trump's 'state of emergency' at the U.S. southern border, 'encouraging resentment'
value.excerpt: Linda Ronstadt bashed Donald Trump and his administration’s handling of the situation at the United States’ southern border.

value.title: Biden faces backlash for saying 'America was an idea' that 'we've never lived up to'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden was facing intense backlash Wednesday night for referring to America as an "idea" that "we've never lived up to."

value.title: Ingraham: Democrats hiding 'true agenda' from middle, working class by trotting out Biden cliches
value.excerpt: President Trump, not Joe Biden, is the candidate who truly fights for the working class, Laura Ingraham argued Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Hunter Biden: Here's what he has said about his Burisma role in Ukraine
value.excerpt: The son of former Vice President Joe Biden has mostly remained mum on the allegations of impropriety while working on the board of Ukrainian oil company Burisma. Here’s what he has said about it in the past.

value.title: Jennifer Lawrence says Trump altered her political views: ‘There’s been a line drawn in the sand’
value.excerpt: Jennifer Lawrence said despite the fact she grew up in a Republican household, because of Trump, she has become more open-minded about politics "based on the things I learned."

value.title: Trump envoy Richard Grenell met with Venezuelan politician in bid to oust Maduro: report
value.excerpt: Richard Grenell, the Trump administration's special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo Peace Negotiations, reportedly tried in September to negotiate with a Venezuelan politician close to the country's strongman president, Nicolas Maduro, in order to obtain the controversial leader's peaceful exit from office.

value.title: Trump grants clemency to Alice Marie Johnson associate, 4 other nonviolent criminals
value.excerpt: President Trump granted clemency on Wednesday to five prisoners-- including one who was an associate of Alice Marie Johnson-- who were each serving time in prison for non-violent offenses.

value.title: Blackburn: Trump should focus on his 'incredible record' at presidential debate, not 'Biden Inc.'
value.excerpt: President Trump should focus on his own accomplishments during Thursday night's second and final presidential debate against Joe Biden, Sen. Marsha Blackburn, R-Tenn., told "Special Report" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump campaign, Nevada GOP threaten to sue Clark County over attempts to ‘obstruct’ election observation
value.excerpt: The campaign and state Republicans claim that observers have been banned from certain areas where ballots are handled.

value.title: Biden drops LA Mayor Eric Garcetti from event after two more men accuse close adviser of sexual misconduct
value.excerpt: Los Angeles Mayor Eric Garcetti’s chances for a cabinet post in a Biden administration are increasingly in doubt now that two more men have accused Garcetti’s close adviser of sexual misconduct.

value.title: Pollster who predicted 2016 result says Trump on track to win again with help of 'hidden' support
value.excerpt: With two weeks left until Election Day, 35 million Americans having already voted, and most polls showing Joe Biden leading President Trump, Trafalgar Group chief pollster Robert Cahaly told “Hannity” Tuesday the incumbent is likely to be reelected.

value.title: Activist group plans widespread, ‘disruptive’ election activities to thwart potential Trump ‘coup’
value.excerpt: 'Trump will not leave office without mass mobilization and direct action,' the group says on its website.

value.title: Trump says 'we're up' in NC amid reported internal worries about keeping state red

value.title: NC governor caught on hot mic telling Biden they'll drag Cal Cunningham ‘across the line’ after scandal
value.excerpt: "I think Cal's going to get across the line, too," Gov. Roy Cooper appeared to say on Monday.

value.title: Trump slams debate moderator Welker as 'terrible,' 'totally partisan'
value.excerpt: President Trump said he is ready for Thursday's debate against Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden, but claimed that it will not be fair because the moderator, NBC's Kristen Welker, will be biased against him.

value.title: Trump urges Barr to 'act fast,' 'appoint somebody' to probe Hunter Biden business dealings
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday said Attorney General William Barr needs to “act” and “appoint somebody” after nearly a dozen House Republicans urged him to tap a special counsel to investigate alleged revelations coming from a laptop purported to have belonged to Joe Biden’s son Hunter.

value.title: Trump to speak to 'Fox & Friends,' two weeks from Election Day
value.excerpt: President Trump will join “Fox & Friends” for an exclusive interview Tuesday at 8 a.m. ET, two weeks out from Election Day.

value.title: Biden backers have looming sense of deja vu
value.excerpt: With multiple polls predicting a clear Biden victory in the November Election, Democrats are getting an uncomfortable sense of déjà vu given that polls in the final weeks of the 2016 election overwhelmingly predicted a victory for Hillary Clinton.

value.title: Why Vice President Pence was in northern Maine on Monday
value.excerpt: When you think of the battlegrounds that could decide whether President Trump or Democratic nominee Joe Biden wins next month’s general election, Maine often doesn’t come to mind.

value.title: Americans say Trump vs. Biden most important election in decades, Gallup poll finds
value.excerpt: A recent Gallup poll found 77% of registered voters said the outcome of the November election between President Trump and Joe Biden matters more to them than prior U.S. elections.

value.excerpt: President Trump has two issues he needs to "hammer home” at the next presidential debate, Fox News contributor Sarah Sanders said on Monday.

value.title: Ratcliffe says Hunter Biden laptop, emails 'not part of some Russian disinformation campaign'
value.excerpt: Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe on Monday said that Hunter Biden’s laptop “is not part of some Russian disinformation campaign,” amid claims from House Intelligence Committee Chairman Adam Schiff suggesting otherwise.

value.title: Trump gives offering while attending Church services in Las Vegas
value.excerpt: As the collection was being taken up, Trump reached into his back pocket a pulled out a number of $20 bills, which he later deposited into a bucket that was being passed around.
